						<summary>

						<p>Pāṇḍya, Māṟavarman Sundarapāṇḍya, 9th year = 13th Century.</p>						

						<p>This records the building of the compound wall with stones and named after Gāṅgēyarāyar. The nagaram of Vallanāḍaṉ-perunderu seems to have contributed something to the construction.</p>						

						<p>[Published in <hi rend="italic">IPS</hi>, No. 468.]</p>						

